But even when loafing as he was this evening , Condy could not rid himself of the thought and recollection of his novel resting or writing , it haunted him . 
Otherwise he would not have been the story writer that he was . 
From now on until he should set down the last sentence , the thing was never to let him alone , never to allow him a moment's peace . 
He could think of nothing else , could talk of nothing else every faculty of his brain , every sense of observation or imagination incessantly concentrated themselves upon this one point . 
Ought to be worked up , you know . 
I've never saved a cent out of my salary . 
